# RTK for terminal / Shell tool

This repo expects **[RTK](https://github.com/rtk-ai/rtk)** when running shell commands from the agent (especially `git`, `cargo`, `pnpm`/`npm`, `docker`, `kubectl`, tests, and linters).

## Golden rule

- Prefix the runnable command with `rtk`: e.g. `rtk git status`, `rtk cargo test`, `rtk pnpm install`.
- In command chains, prefix **each** segment: e.g. `rtk git add .; rtk git commit -m "msg"; rtk git push` (PowerShell) instead of bare `git`.
- If `rtk` is missing from PATH, say so; otherwise still prefer `rtk` whenever it is available.

## Why

On Windows, Cursor’s RTK **preToolUse** hook is bash-based and may not rewrite commands; emitting `rtk ...` directly keeps compact output and avoids relying on the hook.

Extended command list and examples: `%USERPROFILE%\.claude\CLAUDE.md` (RTK section) after `rtk init -g`.
